place.name: SULHAMSTEAD BANNISTER
place.gazetteerText: SULHAMPSTEAD-BANNISTER, a parish in Bradfield district, Berks; 1¾ mile S of Theale r. station. It has a post-office under Reading. Real property, £1,738. Pop., 261. Houses, 54. The living is annexed to Sulhampstead-A. The church is ancient; and there is a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)

place.name: SULHAMSTEAD ABBOTS
place.gazetteerText: SULHAMPSTEAD-ABBOTS, a parish in Bradfield district, Berks; 2 miles S by E of Theale r. station, and 5¾ SW of Reading. Post town, Sulhampstead-Bannister, under Reading. Acres, with S.-B., 2,951. Real property, £2,525. Pop., 357. Houses, 76. S. House is the seat of M. G. Thoyts, Esq. The living is a rectory united with Sulhampstead-B., in the diocese of Oxford. Value, £668. Patron, Queen's College, Oxford. The church is good; and there are a Wesleyan chapel, and charities £25. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)

place.name: SULHAM
place.gazetteerText: SULHAM, a parish in Bradfield district, Berks; 2 miles SSE of Pangbourn r. station, and 4½ W by N of Reading. It has a post-office under Reading. Acres, 6-95. Real property, £1,196. Pop., 118. Houses, 25. S. House is the seat of the Rev. J. Wilder. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Oxford. Value, £198.* Patron, F. Wilder, Esq. The church was rebuilt in 1838. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
